<% content_for :title do %>WhatsApp | <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>Connect WhatsApp Business to <%= installation_brand_name %> via embedded signup, templates, and webhooks.<% end %>

<h1>WhatsApp Business</h1>
<p class="lead">
  WhatsApp inboxes use Meta’s WhatsApp Cloud API. Customers message your business number; agents reply from <%= installation_brand_name %>.
</p>

<h2>Prerequisites</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Meta Business account with permission to manage WhatsApp assets</li>
  <li>WhatsApp embedded signup configured on this installation (operator / Super Admin)</li>
  <li>Phone number not active on consumer WhatsApp app (or migrated properly)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Embedded signup (recommended)</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Settings → Inboxes → Add inbox → WhatsApp</strong></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Connect with WhatsApp Business</strong></li>
  <li>Log in to Meta and select or create WhatsApp Business Account (WABA)</li>
  <li>Grant <code>whatsapp_business_management</code>, <code>whatsapp_business_messaging</code>, <code>business_management</code></li>
  <li>Verify phone number via SMS or voice code</li>
  <li>Add agents as collaborators</li>
  <li>Send test message from a personal phone to your business number</li>
</ol>
<p>Webhooks are configured automatically for embedded signup on supported installations.</p>

<h2>360dialog / Cloud API (manual)</h2>
<p>Some installations support alternate providers (360dialog, manual Cloud API tokens). Follow the provider-specific fields in the inbox setup wizard if embedded signup is unavailable.</p>

<h2>New client setup (no Meta Developer account yet)</h2>
<p>
  Use this flow when a client is starting from zero and has never created a Meta Developer account.
  It helps them prepare the correct values for manual WhatsApp channel setup in <%= installation_brand_name %>.
</p>
<p>
  Useful Meta links:
  <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meta for Developers</a> ·
  <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/apps/" rel="noopener noreferrer">My Apps</a> ·
  <a href="https://business.facebook.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meta Business Manager</a> ·
  <a href="https://business.facebook.com/latest/settings/system_users" rel="noopener noreferrer">System Users</a> ·
  <a href="https://business.facebook.com/wa/manage/home/" rel="noopener noreferrer">WhatsApp Manager</a>
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Open <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meta for Developers</a> and click <strong>Get started</strong> to create a developer account.</li>
  <li>Create (or open) a <strong>Meta Business Manager</strong> account at <a href="https://business.facebook.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer">business.facebook.com</a>.</li>
  <li>In Meta Developer, open <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/apps/" rel="noopener noreferrer">My Apps</a> → <strong>Create App</strong>, choose <strong>Business</strong>, and link the app to their business account.</li>
  <li>Add the <strong>WhatsApp</strong> product, then open <strong>WhatsApp → API Setup</strong> (or <a href="https://business.facebook.com/wa/manage/home/" rel="noopener noreferrer">WhatsApp Manager</a>).</li>
  <li>Add and verify their real business WhatsApp number (SMS/voice code), not just the test number.</li>
  <li>Copy the required values from Meta:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Phone number</strong> (international format, e.g. <code>+2567...</code>)</li>
      <li><strong>Phone number ID</strong></li>
      <li><strong>WhatsApp Business Account ID</strong> (WABA ID)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Create a long-lived <strong>System User</strong> access token in <a href="https://business.facebook.com/latest/settings/system_users" rel="noopener noreferrer">Business Settings → System Users</a> and include WhatsApp permissions; this is the <strong>API key</strong> in <%= installation_brand_name %>.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Values client should send you</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Inbox name</strong> (example: <code>Client Name - WhatsApp</code>)</li>
  <li><strong>Phone number</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Phone number ID</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Business Account ID (WABA)</strong></li>
  <li><strong>API key</strong> (access token)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Manual setup in <%= installation_brand_name %></h3>
<ol>
  <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Inboxes → Add inbox → WhatsApp</strong>.</li>
  <li>Fill all five values exactly as provided by client.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Create WhatsApp Channel</strong>.</li>
  <li>Send a test inbound message to confirm the inbox receives and replies correctly.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Message templates</h2>
<p>Outside the 24-hour customer service window, outbound messages often require <strong>approved templates</strong> in Meta WhatsApp Manager. Create templates for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Order updates</li>
  <li>Appointment reminders</li>
  <li>Follow-ups after resolved tickets</li>
</ul>
<ol>
  <li>Open <a href="https://business.facebook.com/wa/manage/home/" rel="noopener noreferrer">WhatsApp Manager</a> → <strong>Message templates</strong> → <strong>Create template</strong>.</li>
  <li>Choose category (<strong>Utility</strong> or <strong>Marketing</strong> for most campaigns).</li>
  <li>Add template content and placeholders (example: <code>{{1}}</code> customer name).</li>
  <li>Submit and wait for status <strong>Approved</strong> before using in campaigns.</li>
</ol>
<p>After approval, use <a href="<%= guide_page_path('campaigns') %>">WhatsApp campaigns</a> to map variables, choose audience, and schedule sends.</p>

<h2>Session window</h2>
<p>When a customer messages you, a 24-hour session opens where free-form replies are allowed. After it closes, use templates for proactive outreach.</p>

<h2>Inbox configuration</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Reauthorize when Meta tokens expire</li>
  <li>Attach a <%= installation_captain_name %> assistant under <strong><%= installation_captain_name %> → [Assistant] → Inboxes</strong> for AI first-line replies — see <a href="<%= guide_page_path('captain') %>#connect-inbox"><%= installation_captain_name %> on WhatsApp</a></li>
  <li>Or attach a webhook bot under <strong>Settings → Bots</strong></li>
  <li>Enable CSAT on resolve if desired</li>
</ul>

<h2>Quality rating & limits</h2>
<p>Meta rates message quality from user feedback. Low ratings reduce daily send limits. Respond quickly and honor opt-in practices.</p>

<h2>Errors</h2>
<p>See the dedicated <a href="<%= guide_page_path('whatsapp-errors') %>">WhatsApp errors</a> guide for restriction #2655121, OAuth failures, and delivery issues.</p>

